+    // Now, "clear" the ptls buffer, so that this buffer isn't incorrectly rooting objects
+    // in that buffer.
+    ptls->bt_size = 0;","path":"src/gc-alloc-profiler.cpp","position":null,"original_position":23,"commit_id":"77d401f9d87c572ee7022de4761db83892b0bf50","original_commit_id":"581374d25ed68d073086370b60779ab36e0295f9","user":{"login":"vilterp","id":7341,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjczNDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7341?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp","html_url":"https://github.com/vilterp","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/vilterp/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"Hey @vtjnash  — Thanks. You're right that without rooting, some of the pointers recorded here will be unsafe to dereference later.

The problem is, even if we were to fix that problem for this buffer, the backtraces would still be immediately copied to the profiler's vector of allocations, which isn't rooted either: https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/blob/1ad2396f05fa63a71e5842c814791cd7c7715100/src/gc-alloc-profiler.cpp#L30

So we'd have to fix it there too for these pointers to be safely unpacked and dereferenced.

We spent a bunch of time in https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/42768 trying to figure out how to root that buffer, before noticing that the CPU profiler just sidesteps this problem — it doesn't root the main buffer, and just renders stack frames it can't dereference as `unknown`. In practice, with the alloc profiler as well as the CPU profiler, there haven't been too many `unknown` frames. So, we ultimately mimicked the CPU profiler.

I filed https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43796 to address this for both the CPU and alloc profiler — a bigger project which may involve special-casing the GC to scan both their backtrace buffers, as well as these intermediate buffers. In the meantime, I think 1.8 would be in pretty good shape if we fix this thread safety bug but not fix the few `unknown`s.","created_at":"2022-02-18T06:14:14Z","updated_at":"2022-02-18T06:14:15Z","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44116#discussion_r809702686","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/44116","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments/809702686"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44116#discussion_r809702686"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/44116"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments/809702686/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":null,"original_start_line":65,"start_side":"RIGHT","line":null,"original_line":67,"side":"RIGHT","in_reply_to_id":808517526},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/44116","id":846000226,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM4ybPBi","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44116","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44116.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/44116.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/44116","number":44116,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Fix thread-safety violation in Allocations Profiler: Create a new per-thread backtrace buffer in ptls","user":{"login":"NHDaly","id":1582097,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1ODIwOTc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1582097?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NHDaly","html_url":"https: